place.name: BRADESTON
place.gazetteerText: BRADESTON, a parish in Blofield district, Norfolk; on the Yarmouth railway and the river Yare, ½ a mile E of Brundall r. station, and 4 WSW of Acle. Post Town, Blofield, under Norwich. Acres, 516. Real property, £1,183. Pop., 133. Houses, 31. The living is a rectory, annexed to the rectory of Strumpshaw, in the diocese of Norwich. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
